A Celebration of the Films
We Cant Forget, From the Editors of
ENTERTAINMENT WEEKLY

"May the Force be with you."
"Rosebud." "You talkin' to me?" Before many of us could write a complete sentence, we were repeating catchphrases like these. And small wonder. They belong to the films whose images and moments and grandeur we all share. What classical myths were to ancient Greece and Rome, movies have become for us: a pantheon of heroes and villains against whom we measure ourselves, a world of epic struggle made human and everyday virtue writ large
